He was involved in conspiracies around the world, a senior official who wanted to remain anonymous noted, pointing to the delicate nature of the U.S. airstrikes on Pakistani soil.
Assuming its central role as given, this also included planning attacks against the US and Europe.
He took strategic instructions from al Qaeda’s top leaders and implemented them in operational planning for possible terrorist attacks.
The second U.S. official said that Somali had quickly risen in the Al Qaeda hierarchy and maintained best connections to other extremist groups in the region.
He may not be known to some Americans, the second official said, but this in no way reduces the danger he posed to us and our allies.
