US Secretary of Defense Gates: Iran must expect additional sanctions
Defense Secretary Robert M. Gates said Friday that world powers will soon impose “significant additional sanctions” on Iran for not participating in talks about its nuclear plans.
Gates spoke to a group of about 300 U.S. soldiers in northern Iraq during a 7-day tour of the war zones in Afghanistan and Iraq, downplaying the prospect of a military action against the Islamic Republic of Iran.
