A British programmer gets an annual gross salary of 45,226 euros and a Frenchman 31,059, as opposed to the 24,000 euros a Spaniard earns.
As a result, a truck driver has an annual net salary of 34,247 euros in England, 25,751 in France and 16,420 euros in Spain.
