Among other assets, it already has its largest wind farm (192 MW) in Victoria and leads the group of companies commissioned to build and manage the Adelaide desalination plant with a budget of 700 million.
His intention now is to consolidate in these two areas and to use these synergies to gain access to the construction and infrastructure branches.
The underground toll road, which is promoted by the Brisbane City Infrastructure Office and is called Northern Link, is intended to connect the western highway in Toowong with the Kelvin Grove bypass road (see map) over a length of 5 kilometres through tunnels, the largest measure of congestion reduction on the Brisbane roads.
The timetable issued by the city administration provides for the award of the contract for summer 2010 and the start of construction work in December next year.
Even if this toll road is already expected to open up to traffic in the last months of 2014, it is expected that the construction work will continue until 2016.
The tunnel was designed in 2005.
It has two lanes in each direction, an electronic toll system and a complex ventilation system.
