The cars with historical value, on the other hand, may be registered again, even if they have been deregistered after difficult administrative procedures.
Workshop cost estimate in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in only four steps: identifying the vehicle, searching for the spare part, creating and creating a cost estimate.
The ease of use of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an internet connection to use it.
After the model to be repaired has been identified on the basis of the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the working hours, surcharges or discounts and after that he can have the cost estimate printed out and passed on to his customer.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for assessment like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalog.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount that the customer can easily pay.
At the moment, Audatex is working on offering these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that car mechanics have been waiting for for a long time, because you can use it to select a door, for example, and then turn the picture completely around to look at the inside.
